Victor Tasca  Cyberbullying  13/02/2024 3^D 

In the modern era, cyberbullying is an everyday problem, regarding specifically young but also uneducated people (on the technological point of view). It’s important to create an environment which is both positive for people, which prioritizes knowledge and mutual feelings: it’s not the real world, it’s virtual. This one is a problem which is not seen in real life but it’s something more subtle, because the consequences are often more moral rather than physical. 

In this world, people tend to judge others based on their looks rather than their feelings. These people can joke with their emotions without respecting their right to be different. Safety must be a common practice in online communications and in meeting new people: avoid publishing personal data, report hurtful activity which can be dangerous for other people and prevent undesired people from interfering without losing their respect.  

There is a general lack of education, both on the emotional and the IT side: online people miss empathy, and they don’t realize the consequences of being behind a keyboard. It’s the main reason why so many people don’t talk about this problem, and finding people educated on the topic, specifically on the psychological manipulation and the symptoms deriving from it.
